               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18160214-41-person489">
                  ROBERT 
                  COMBES
               <interp inst="t18160214-41-person489" type="surname" value="COMBES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18160214-41-person489" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18160214-41-person489" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18160214-41-viclabel237" type="occupation">clerk in the Bank of England</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18160214-41-victim488 t18160214-41-viclabel237"></join>. I lost my handkerchief on the 6th February, in <placeName id="t18160214-41-crimeloc238">Cornhill</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18160214-41-crimeloc238" type="placeName" value="Cornhill"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18160214-41-crimeloc238" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18160214-41-off235 t18160214-41-crimeloc238"></join>, at about a quarter before five in the afternoon. I was looking into a bookseller's shop under the Royal Exchange. I felt something at my coat pocket, and on putting my hand to it. I missed my pocket handkerchief. I turned round, and saw a boy run round the corner. I ran after him. On Cornhill he dropped the handkerchief. I followed him through Change Alley into Lombard-street, and in Abchurch-lane somebody stopped him. I took him immediately to the Mansion-house, and left him in custody of the officers. I am satisfied he is the boy.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18160214-41-person490">
                  JOHN 
                  CLARE
